#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.70"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.70:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.70:0.2"
msgid "7. Migajālavagga "
msgstr "7. With Migajāla "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 70. Upavāṇasandiṭṭhikasutta → upavāṇasuttaṃ (bj) | upavāna (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.70:0.3"
msgid "70. Upavāṇasandiṭṭhikasutta "
msgstr "70. Upavāṇa on What is Visible in This Very Life "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn35.70:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upavāṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … "
msgstr "Then Venerable Upavāṇa went up to the Buddha … "

#. VAR: upavāṇo → upavāno (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.70:1.2"
msgid "ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā upavāṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.70:1.3"
msgid "“‘sandiṭṭhiko dhammo, sandiṭṭhiko dhammo’ti, bhante, vuccati. "
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of ‘a teaching visible in this very life’. "

msgctxt "sn35.70:1.4"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, sandiṭṭhiko dhammo hoti, akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhī”ti? "
msgstr "In what way is the teaching visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.70:2.1"
msgid "“Idha pana, upavāṇa, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā rūpappaṭisaṃvedī ca hoti rūparāgappaṭisaṃvedī ca. "
msgstr "“Upavāṇa, take a mendicant who sees a sight with their eyes. They experience both the sight and the desire for the sight. "

msgctxt "sn35.70:2.2"
msgid "Santañca ajjhattaṃ rūpesu rāgaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ rūpesu rāgo’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "There is desire for sights in them, and they understand that. "

msgctxt "sn35.70:2.3"
msgid "Yaṃ taṃ, upavāṇa, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā rūpappaṭisaṃvedī ca hoti rūparāgappaṭisaṃvedī ca. "
msgstr "Since this is so, "

msgctxt "sn35.70:2.4"
msgid "Santañca ajjhattaṃ rūpesu rāgaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ rūpesu rāgo’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.70:2.5"
msgid "Evampi kho, upavāṇa, sandiṭṭhiko dhammo hoti akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhi … pe …. "
msgstr "this is how the teaching is visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.42, sc3
msgctxt "sn35.70:3.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, upavāṇa, bhikkhu jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā rasappaṭisaṃvedī ca hoti rasarāgappaṭisaṃvedī ca. "
msgstr "Next, take a mendicant who hears … smells … tastes … touches … "

msgctxt "sn35.70:3.2"
msgid "Santañca ajjhattaṃ rasesu rāgaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ rasesu rāgo’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.70:3.3"
msgid "Yaṃ taṃ, upavāṇa, bhikkhu jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā rasappaṭisaṃvedī ca hoti rasarāgappaṭisaṃvedī ca. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.70:3.4"
msgid "Santañca ajjhattaṃ rasesu rāgaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ rasesu rāgo’ti pajānāti. Evampi kho, upavāṇa, sandiṭṭhiko dhammo hoti akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhi … pe …. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.70:4.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, upavāṇa, bhikkhu manasā dhammaṃ viññāya dhammappaṭisaṃvedī ca hoti dhammarāgappaṭisaṃvedī ca. "
msgstr "Next, take a mendicant who knows a thought with their mind. They experience both the thought and the desire for the thought. "

msgctxt "sn35.70:4.2"
msgid "Santañca ajjhattaṃ dhammesu rāgaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ dhammesu rāgo’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "There is desire for thoughts in them, and they understand that. "

msgctxt "sn35.70:4.3"
msgid "Yaṃ taṃ, upavāṇa, bhikkhu manasā dhammaṃ viññāya dhammappaṭisaṃvedī ca hoti dhammarāgappaṭisaṃvedī ca. "
msgstr "Since this is so, "

msgctxt "sn35.70:4.4"
msgid "Santañca ajjhattaṃ dhammesu rāgaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ dhammesu rāgo’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.70:4.5"
msgid "Evampi kho, upavāṇa, sandiṭṭhiko dhammo hoti … pe … paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhi … pe …. "
msgstr "this is how the teaching is visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn35.70:5.1"
msgid "Idha pana, upavāṇa, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā rūpappaṭisaṃvedī ca hoti, no ca rūparāgappaṭisaṃvedī. "
msgstr "Take a mendicant who sees a sight with their eyes. They experience the sight but no desire for the sight. "

msgctxt "sn35.70:5.2"
msgid "Asantañca ajjhattaṃ rūpesu rāgaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ rūpesu rāgo’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "There is no desire for sights in them, and they understand that. "

msgctxt "sn35.70:5.3"
msgid "Yaṃ taṃ, upavāṇa, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā rūpappaṭisaṃvedīhi kho hoti, no ca rūparāgappaṭisaṃvedī. "
msgstr "Since this is so, "

msgctxt "sn35.70:5.4"
msgid "Asantañca ajjhattaṃ rūpesu rāgaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ rūpesu rāgo’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.70:5.5"
msgid "Evampi kho, upavāṇa, sandiṭṭhiko dhammo hoti, akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhi … pe …. "
msgstr "this is how the teaching is visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn35.70:6.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, upavāṇa, bhikkhu jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā rasappaṭisaṃvedīhi kho hoti, no ca rasarāgappaṭisaṃvedī. Asantañca ajjhattaṃ rasesu rāgaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ rasesu rāgo’ti pajānāti … pe …. "
msgstr "Next, take a mendicant who hears … smells … tastes … touches … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.43, sc7
msgctxt "sn35.70:7.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, upavāṇa, bhikkhu manasā dhammaṃ viññāya dhammappaṭisaṃvedīhi kho hoti, no ca dhammarāgappaṭisaṃvedī. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.70:7.2"
msgid "Asantañca ajjhattaṃ dhammesu rāgaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ dhammesu rāgo’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.70:7.3"
msgid "Yaṃ taṃ, upavāṇa, bhikkhu manasā dhammaṃ viññāya dhammappaṭisaṃvedīhi kho hoti, no ca dhammarāgappaṭisaṃvedī. "
msgstr "Next, take a mendicant who knows a thought with their mind. They experience the thought but no desire for the thought. "

msgctxt "sn35.70:7.4"
msgid "Asantañca ajjhattaṃ dhammesu rāgaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ dhammesu rāgo’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "There is no desire for thoughts in them, and they understand that. "

msgctxt "sn35.70:7.5"
msgid "Evampi kho, upavāṇa, sandiṭṭhiko dhammo hoti, akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhī”ti. "
msgstr "Since this is so, this is how the teaching is visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.70:7.6"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

